  "text": "near the Schwarzschild radius. Although the first-order correction to the areal radius R is comparable to the 0th-order term (given by the Schwarzschild solution) at small z, no higher-order correction is of a comparable order of magnitude [CITATION_1] . Hence, after the coordinate transformation to the tortoise coordinate, the solution above reproduces eqs.(2.16) and (2.17) .",
